  "chapter": {
    "number": 3,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Judgment on Jerusalem and Judah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For behold, the Lord GOD of Hosts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is about to remove",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "from Jerusalem and Judah",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "both supply",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2515
          },
          {
            "text": "and support:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the whole supply of food and water,",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "the mighty man and the warrior,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the judge and the prophet,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the soothsayer and the elder,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "the commander of fifty and the dignitary,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the counselor, the cunning magician, and the clever enchanter.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I will make mere lads their leaders,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and children will rule over them.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The people will oppress one another,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "man against man, neighbor against neighbor;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the young will rise up against the old,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the base against the honorable.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A man will seize his brother",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "within his father’s house:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“You have a cloak—you be our leader!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Take charge of this heap of rubble.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "On that day he will cry aloud:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“I am not a healer.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2516
          },
          {
            "text": "I have no food or clothing in my house.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Do not make me leader of the people!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For Jerusalem has stumbled",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Judah has fallen",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because they spoke and acted against the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "defying His glorious presence.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2517
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The expression on their faces testifies against them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and like Sodom they flaunt their sin;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they do not conceal it.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Woe to them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for they have brought disaster upon themselves.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Tell the righteous it will be well with them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for they will enjoy the fruit of their labor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to the wicked; disaster is upon them!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "For they will be repaid with what their hands have done.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Youths oppress My people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and women rule over them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "O My people, your guides mislead you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they turn you from your paths.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD arises to contend;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He stands to judge the people.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD brings this charge",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "against the elders and leaders of His people:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“You have devoured the vineyard;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the plunder of the poor is in your houses.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why do you crush My people",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and grind the faces of the poor?”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the Lord GOD of Hosts."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Warning to the Daughters of Zion"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD also says:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Because the daughters of Zion are haughty—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "walking with heads held high",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and wanton eyes,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "prancing and skipping as they go,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "jingling the bracelets on their ankles—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "the Lord will bring sores",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "on the heads of the daughters of Zion,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the LORD will make their foreheads bare.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2518
          },
          {
            "text": "”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In that day the Lord will take away their finery:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their anklets and headbands and crescents;",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "their pendants, bracelets, and veils;",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "their headdresses, ankle chains, and sashes;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "their perfume bottles and charms;",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "their signet rings and nose rings;",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "their festive robes, capes, cloaks, and purses;",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "and their mirrors, linen garments, tiaras, and shawls.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Instead of fragrance",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there will be a stench;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "instead of a belt, a rope;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "instead of styled hair, baldness;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "instead of fine clothing, sackcloth;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "instead of beauty, shame.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2519
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your men will fall by the sword,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your warriors in battle.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And the gates of Zion will lament and mourn;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "destitute, she will sit on the ground.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
